Yep.

In my view, the Archivist's job is to ensure that none of Agora's official
history risks getting lost.  If e does eir job to this spirit, I say e
deserves eir Salary (if not more), and should be kept.

Of course, there might be strong suspicions around that prior Archivists
have not done their job properly, and so parts of our history _have_ been
lost.  Unfortunately the job description has never included what I
consider to be its real spirit.

For example, given the fact that Players have often dropped out of the
game without warning, this plainly and obviously demands occasional extra
backups placed in the care of other Players than the Archivist.

Greetings,
Ørjan.

