By 'a message containing votes' I don't mean 'a message containing
a description of votes', but rather 'a message whose effect is
actually to cast votes'. But I take your point that this is not clear
enough. If I don't make this distinction clearly enough, the Rule
will also conflict with the discussion provisions in R1023. I don't
think there's any point in trying to prevent people from discussing
their votes, both for the reason that it's a bad idea, and that even
if it were a good idea, it would be impossible.


